From 7e7e4fbd53c7204e399f4ea531f9f0f25c400507 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vignesh C <vignc@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Sep 2025 15:30:49 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:CP wifi:ath12k Advertise single channel operation
 capability

Advertise that the target supports single channel operation by
setting the IEEE80211_HW_SUPPORTS_SINGLE_CHANNEL hardware flag
during hw registration.

This capability indicates that the hardware is designed to operate
on a single channel at a time, which is relevant for scenarios
where concurrent multi-channel operation is not feasible or desired.
By exposing this flag to mac80211, upper layers can make informed
decisions about channel assignment and synchronization.

Signed-off-by: Vignesh C <vignc@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
index 8362c3d..15908a6 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -22035,6 +22035,7 @@ static int ath12k_mac_hw_register(struct ath12k_hw *ah)
 	ieee80211_hw_set(hw, HAS_TX_QUEUE);
 	ieee80211_hw_set(hw, SUPPORTS_DSCP_TID_MAP);
 	ieee80211_hw_set(hw, SUPPORTS_MULTI_BSSID);
+	ieee80211_hw_set(hw, SUPPORTS_SINGLE_CHANNEL);
 
 	if (ath12k_frame_mode == ATH12K_HW_TXRX_ETHERNET) {
 		ieee80211_hw_set(hw, SUPPORTS_TX_ENCAP_OFFLOAD);
-- 
